## MASTER_PLAN.md
Seven milestones organized as vertical feature slices with DAG ordering, plus 
coverage matrices mapping every PRD endpoint, page, and business rule to 
exactly one milestone.

## Milestone breakdown

| # | Name | Template | Group | Deps | ACs |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| M1 | Platform Foundation | full_stack | — | none | 0 (infra) |
| M2 | Auth & Session | full_stack | — | M1 | 6 |
| M3 | Projects Management | full_stack | A | M2 | 7 |
| M4 | Tasks Core & State Machine | full_stack | B | M3 | 8 |
| M5 | Task Views: Kanban & Table | full_stack | C | M4 | 6 |
| M6 | Comments on Tasks | full_stack | C | M4 | 4 |
| M7 | Team Members & Seed Data | full_stack | C | M2, M4 | 5 |

## Key design decisions
- **All four PRD entities covered**: User (M2+M7), Project (M3), Task (M4+M5), 
Comment (M6).
- **All 8 business rules mapped**: BR-001→M3, BR-002→M2, BR-003/004→M4, 
BR-005→M3 (with M4 listener), BR-006→M2/M7, BR-007→M1 utility used everywhere, 
BR-008→M1 shared DTO.
- **Shared-file collision avoidance**: M1 creates registries (`app.module.ts`, 
locale files, nav registry, `ProjectArchiver` extension point); later 
milestones contribute via declaration files rather than editing shared files 
directly.
- **Task state machine** fully encoded in M4 with exhaustive role-guarded 
transitions; M5 consumes it via UI-only button visibility logic.
- **i18n/RTL discipline**: every feature milestone declares its own locale 
shard merged at build time; logical CSS enforced by M1 lint rule.

